<p>Traditional split-system air conditioners paired with high-efficiency gas furnaces remain popular choices for Kansas City homes, particularly those with existing natural gas connections. Gas furnaces with AFUE ratings of 90% or higher provide reliable heating during harsh winter conditions, while variable-speed air conditioning systems with SEER ratings of 16+ ensure comfortable cooling without excessive energy consumption. Ductless mini-split systems work well for home additions, sunrooms, or older homes without existing ductwork, offering zone-based temperature control ideal for Kansas City's variable seasonal demands.</p>

