<p>Newer developments in western Kansas City, including areas near Kansas City Kansas Community College, typically feature modern homes with simpler rooflines perfect for standard solar installations. These neighborhoods often have newer HVAC systems but can benefit from smart thermostat upgrades and zoning systems to optimize energy usage with solar production. The Argentine district, undergoing significant revitalization, presents opportunities for comprehensive energy efficiency upgrades combining solar installations with complete HVAC system replacements, maximizing both comfort and energy savings for residents investing in neighborhood growth.</p>

